messages.speech: Self-Employment taxes are your contributions to Social Security and Medicare if you work for yourself. This rate is currently 15.3% for anyone who earned over $400 being self-employed. To avoid a penalty, you'll want to pay this tax quarterly to the IRS.

messages.title: Want me to estimate your self-employment taxes?
